---
layout: layouts/element.njk
title: "article"
description: "Self-contained, independently distributable content such as blog posts, news articles, forum posts, product cards, or user comments."
elementName: article
category: native
nativeGroup: Sectioning
currentPath: /docs/elements/native/article/
permalink: /docs/elements/native/article/
---

{% set defaultCode %}<article>
  <header>
    <h2>Article Title</h2>
    <p>Published on <time datetime="2024-01-15">January 15, 2024</time></p>
  </header>
  <p>This is the main content of the article.</p>
  <footer>
    <p>Written by Jane Doe</p>
  </footer>
</article>{% endset %}

{% set blogCode %}<article class="blog">
  <header>
    <h2>How to Write Better Articles</h2>
    <p><time datetime="2024-01-15">January 15, 2024</time> in Writing</p>
  </header>
  <p>Writing compelling articles requires understanding
  your audience, structuring your thoughts clearly,
  and revising thoroughly.</p>
  <footer>
    <p>By Jane Doe | 5 min read</p>
  </footer>
</article>{% endset %}

{% set cardCode %}<article class="card">
  <h3>Product Feature Update</h3>
  <p>We have released new features that improve
  performance by 40% and add dark mode support.</p>
  <a href="#">Read more</a>
</article>{% endset %}

{% set featureCode %}<article class="feature">
  <header>
    <h2>Introducing Vanilla Breeze</h2>
    <p>A layered HTML component system for modern
    web development</p>
  </header>
  <p>Build accessible, performant websites with native
  HTML elements enhanced through progressive CSS styling.</p>
</article>{% endset %}

{% set compactCode %}<article class="compact">
  <img src="thumb.jpg" alt="Thumbnail" />
  <section>
    <h3>Getting Started with CSS Grid</h3>
    <p>Learn the fundamentals of CSS Grid layout.</p>
  </section>
</article>{% endset %}

{% set nestedCode %}<article>
  <header>
    <strong>User123</strong>
    <time datetime="2024-01-15T10:30">10:30 AM</time>
  </header>
  <p>This is a great article! Thanks for sharing.</p>

  <article class="nested">
    <header>
      <strong>Author</strong>
      <time datetime="2024-01-15T11:00">11:00 AM</time>
    </header>
    <p>Thank you for the kind words!</p>
  </article>
</article>{% endset %}

{% set numberedCode %}<article data-numbered>
  <h2>Origins of Movable Type</h2>
  <p>Movable type was first developed in China...</p>
  <h3>Gutenberg's Press</h3>
  <p>Johannes Gutenberg independently invented...</p>
  <h2>The Typographic Tradition</h2>
  <figure>
    <img src="press.jpg" alt="Historical printing press" />
    <figcaption>A reconstructed printing press.</figcaption>
  </figure>
</article>{% endset %}

{% set dropCapCode %}<article data-drop-cap>
  <p>When the first rays of morning light crept through
  the cathedral windows, they illuminated row upon row
  of hand-set lead type...</p>
</article>{% endset %}

{% set proseCode %}<article data-prose>
  <p>
    <img src="meadow.jpg" alt="Wildflowers" />
    The alpine meadows above the treeline host an
    extraordinary diversity of wildflowers during the
    brief summer season...
  </p>
</article>{% endset %}

{% set highlightsCode %}<article data-highlights>
  <p>Select any text in this article to highlight it.
  Choose a color from the toolbar that appears above
  your selection.</p>
</article>{% endset %}

{% set highlightsColorsCode %}<article data-highlights data-highlights-colors="yellow,green,blue,pink">
  <!-- Define custom property for each color name -->
  <style>
    article { --highlight-yellow: #fef08a; }
  </style>
  <p>Custom highlight palette.</p>
</article>{% endset %}

{% set highlightsReadonlyCode %}<article data-highlights data-highlights-readonly>
  <p>Renders stored highlights without allowing new ones.</p>
</article>{% endset %}

{% set jsApiExample %}import { initHighlights } from 'vanilla-breeze';

const ctrl = initHighlights(document.querySelector('[data-highlights]'));
ctrl.getHighlights();        // Array of highlight objects
ctrl.removeHighlight(id);    // Remove by ID
ctrl.clearAll();             // Remove all
ctrl.exportHighlights();     // JSON string
ctrl.importHighlights(json); // Restore from backup
ctrl.destroy();              // Cleanup listeners{% endset %}

<section>
    <h2>Usage</h2>
    <p>Use the <code>&lt;article&gt;</code> element for content that:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Makes sense on its own, outside the context of the page</li>
      <li>Could be syndicated or shared independently (RSS, social media)</li>
      <li>Represents a complete, self-contained composition</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Common uses include blog posts, news articles, product cards, forum posts, comments, and widgets.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Examples</h2>

    <h3>Default</h3>
    <p>Basic article with header and content.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/article-default.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/article" title="Default article" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Default article">{{ defaultCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.blog</h3>
    <p>Optimized for long-form reading with constrained width (65ch).</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/article-blog.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/article/blog" title="Blog article" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Blog article">{{ blogCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.card</h3>
    <p>Card-style article with border, background, and padding.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/article-card.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/article/card" title="Card article" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Card article">{{ cardCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.feature</h3>
    <p>Hero-style feature article with centered header.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/article-feature.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/article/feature" title="Feature article" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Feature article">{{ featureCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.compact</h3>
    <p>Compact list-item style for article listings.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/article-compact.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/article/compact" title="Compact article" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Compact article">{{ compactCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>.nested</h3>
    <p>Nested articles for comments and replies with indentation.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/article-nested.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/article/nested" title="Nested article" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Nested article">{{ nestedCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>data-numbered</h3>
    <p>Academic-style auto-numbering for headings, figures, and tables. CSS counters automatically prefix h2-h4 headings with hierarchical numbers, and prepend "Figure" / "Table" labels to captions.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/article-numbered.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/article/numbered" title="Auto-numbered article" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Auto-numbered article">{{ numberedCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>data-drop-cap</h3>
    <p>Adds a large decorative initial letter to the opening paragraph, a convention borrowed from illuminated manuscripts and editorial print design.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/article-drop-cap.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/article/drop-cap" title="Drop cap article" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Drop cap article">{{ dropCapCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>data-prose</h3>
    <p>Automatically floats images that appear inside paragraphs to the inline-end, sized to half the content width. Ideal for markdown or CMS-generated content where images are placed directly within paragraph text.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/article-prose.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/article/prose" title="Prose mode article" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Prose mode article">{{ proseCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>data-highlights</h3>
    <p>Enables Medium-style text highlighting and private notes. Select text to see a floating toolbar with color swatches. Click an existing highlight to change color, add a note, or remove it. Highlights persist in localStorage.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/article-highlights.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/article/highlights" title="Article with highlights" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Article with highlights">{{ highlightsCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>data-highlights (custom colors)</h3>
    <p>Use <code>data-highlights-colors</code> to provide a custom palette and define matching <code>--highlight-{name}</code> custom properties.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/article-highlights-colors.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/article/highlights/colors" title="Custom highlight colors" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Custom highlight colors">{{ highlightsColorsCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>data-highlights (readonly)</h3>
    <p>Add <code>data-highlights-readonly</code> to render stored highlights without allowing new ones.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/article-highlights-readonly.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/article/highlights/readonly" title="Readonly highlights" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Readonly highlights">{{ highlightsReadonlyCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

